The NEWS file for the Davit package.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.2 -- 27 March 2026

Changes:
  Modified davit(1) to set the Archive e-mail address as the envelope sender
  when originating e-mail.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.1 -- 27 March 2026

Changes:
   Modified policy in davit(1) so that Affidavit Reminder e-mails will no
   longer to blind-copied to the Archive e-mail address.

   Fixed a bug in davit(1) where the 'List Contacts', 'List Program List'
   and 'Show Affiliate History' dialogs could display in a collapsed state.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.0rc5 -- 3 December 2025

Changes:
   Package dependencies. Added a 'wireguard-tools' dependency to the
   'davit-gui' DEB package.

   Same configuration. Fixed typos in the '[Wireguard]' section of the
   sample davit.conf(5) file.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.0rc4 -- 3 December 2025

Changes:
   Documentation. Fixed a typo in the davit.conf(5) man page.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.0rc3 -- 30 September 2025

Changes:
   Wireguard VPN Support. Added a 'ConnectionPriority=' directive to
   davit.conf(5) to allow for various VPN failover scenarios. See the
   '[Wireguard]' section of the davit.conf(5) man page for details.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.0rc2 -- 25 September 2025

Changes:
   Wireguard VPN Support. Davit(1) can now be configured to automatically
   bring up Wireguard VPN tunnels at startup and take them down at exit.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.0rc1 -- 3 September 2025

Changes:
   Various bugfixes. See the ChangeLog.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
v3.0.0rc0a -- 14 August 2025

Changes:
   Toolkit Changes. Ported code to use Qt6.
 -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
